## How it works…

The use of raw MathML without the `MathJax` library will not work on most browsers, but with the library, the output is automatically rendered either as an SVG or as a standard image. In the MathML example, we use XML nesting to designate where the elements will be contained, and elements such as `mrow` and `mfrac` are all defined in the MathML namespace ([http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML](http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML)) with a root element called `math`. Although the concept is very simple, in practice it is extremely hard to create expressions like this one without the help of external software.

An additional downside to MathML is the fact that it is not fully supported in all browsers.
